parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Nominative Feminine Singular
str2: To have, hold, possess. Including an alternate form scheo skheh'-o; a primary verb; to hold.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To cry aloud, shriek. A primary verb; properly, to 'croak' or scream, i.e. to call aloud.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Nominative Feminine Singular
str2: To be in travail, suffer birth-pangs. From odin; to experience the pains of parturition.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Middle or Passive - Nominative Feminine Singular
str2: To examine, as by torture; I torment; I buffet, as of waves. From basanos; to torture.
A strengthened form of a primary teko tek'-o; to produce, literally or figuratively.
